#!/usr/bin/env bash
# .githooks/commit-msg
#
# Validates that feat/fix commits include the required protocol trailers
# (Edge-Cases / Score / Align / Craft / Codex-Reviewed / Decisions /
# Compliance-Check) per scripts/protocol-gate.ts.
#
# To bypass for an emergency: add the trailer
#   Protocol-Skip: <>=10-char reason>
# to the commit message. The skip is logged to docs/protocol-skips.jsonl
# and surfaces in CI as an audit line.
#
# Activated via: git config core.hooksPath .githooks  (run setup once).
#
# 2026-05-15 audit caught the prior version silently `exit 0`-ing when
# bun was missing from PATH. On a fresh Windows dev machine without
# bun installed, EVERY commit bypassed the protocol-gate trailer
# enforcement with only a printed warning. Softer than --no-verify,
# equally invisible. Per the user's mandate "never skip the gates,"
# missing bun now HARD-FAILS with install instructions.

set -e

if ! command -v bun >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  cat <<'EOM' >&2

[commit-msg] FAIL: bun not on PATH.

The protocol-gate trailer validator runs under bun. The commit-msg
hook cannot silently skip; the audit caught that pattern as a
Windows-machine bypass.

Install bun:
  - macOS / Linux: curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash
  - Windows:       powershell -c "irm bun.sh/install.ps1 | iex"
  - npm fallback:  npm install -g bun

Then re-run the commit. For a genuine emergency where bun cannot be
installed (CI bootstrap, sandbox without network), use
`git commit --no-verify` and explain in the commit message body --
the bypass is auditable in git log + CI.

EOM
  exit 1
fi

bun run scripts/protocol-gate.ts --commit-msg "$1"
